snippet.textDisplay:
As someone who has been in theatre for almost their entire life I can agree with the hierarchy.

I, as someone who is kinda a mix of musical kid and tech kid is in the semi-annoying vein despite being in the crew/tech area of production.

All of my fellow techies are indeed just like “nah bro I don’t wanna be on stage I just wanna... move this desk.”

My best friend is the musical kid and absolutely fits what you said. If I had a nickel for every Hamilton/DEH/BMC/Heathers/Mean Girls/Beetlejuice song she’s ever sung I would honestly be a millionaire by now.
